Code preview of table PARAMETER

if exists (select 1
from sys.sysreferences r join sys.sysobjects o on (o.id = r.constid and o.type = 'F')
where r.fkeyid = object_id('PARAMETER') and o.name = 'FK_PARAMETE_REFERENCE_SOURCE')
alter table PARAMETER
drop constraint FK_PARAMETE_REFERENCE_SOURCE
go

if exists (select 1
from sysobjects
where id = object_id('PARAMETER')
and type = 'U')
drop table PARAMETER
go

/*==============================================================*/
/* Table: PARAMETER */
/*==============================================================*/
create table PARAMETER (
SOURCE varchar(20) not null,
PARAMETER varchar(20) not null,
ID_ORDER int null,
TYPE varchar(20) null default 'DIRECT'
constraint CKC_TYPE_PARAMETE check (TYPE is null or (TYPE in ('DIRECT','PROPERTY'))),
SQLTYPE varchar(20) null
constraint CKC_SQLTYPE_PARAMETE check (SQLTYPE is null or (SQLTYPE in ('VARCHAR','LONGVARCHAR','NUMERIC','DECIMAL','BIT','TINYINT','SMALLINT','INTEGER','BIGINT','REAL','FLOAT','DOUBLE','BINARY','VARBINARY','LONGVARBINARY','DATE','TIME','TIMESTAMP'))),
IS_MULTIVALUE varchar(10) null default 'NO'
constraint CKC_IS_MULTIVALUE_PARAMETE check (IS_MULTIVALUE is null or (IS_MULTIVALUE in ('YES','NO'))),
VALUE varchar(1000) null,
constraint PK_PARAMETER primary key nonclustered (SOURCE, PARAMETER)
)
go
